main event: A witness observed a large, bell-shaped object hovering about 75 feet off the ground in El Paso, Texas on November 4, 1957.
interesting points: The object had a whirring sound similar to a small car engine.
The object then went away over the mountains.
The observer's car stalled and all lights dimmed when the object was present.
The object passed over the observer's car at 2000 feet altitude, moving slowly on a westerly heading and changing altitude at irregular intervals.
When the object reached the Franklin Mountains, it lifted vertically.
